---

<ToolLayout
  title="Chinese Character Counter"
  description="Count Chinese characters, English words, and analyze text frequency. See detailed statistics including unique characters, reading time estimate, and character frequency chart."
  language="chinese"
  toolSlug="character-counter"
  faq={faq}
  relatedTools={relatedTools}
  relatedArticles={relatedArticles}
>
  <CharacterCounter client:load />

  <Fragment slot="about">
    <section class="mt-10 mb-8 prose max-w-none">
      <h2>About This Character Counter</h2>
      <p>Paste any Chinese text to get a comprehensive analysis including total characters, Chinese character count, unique characters, English words, punctuation, and estimated reading time. The tool also generates a visual frequency chart showing which characters appear most often.</p>
      <h3>Why Character Counting Matters</h3>
      <p>Chinese character counting is essential for students tracking their vocabulary growth, writers meeting word count requirements, and translators estimating project scope. Unlike English where spaces separate words, Chinese text flows continuously, making automated counting tools especially useful.</p>
      <h3>Character Frequency Analysis</h3>
      <p>The frequency chart helps you identify which characters appear most often in your text. This is a great way to discover high-frequency characters you should prioritize in your studies. Click any character in the chart to hear its pronunciation.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</ToolLayout>
